test
### Create a docker image on local
Create a Dockerfile, with steps to add the app using node:18 base image

```shell
docker build -t asset-testing .
```
```shell
#Verify the image from local
docker run -it -p 8005:8080 asset-testing
```

```shell
#Create tag and push to docker hub
docker tag asset-testing alahari9/asset-testing:latest
docker push alahari9/asset-testing:latest
```


```shell
#create a k8s deployment
# create a helm/templates directory
mkdir -p helm/templates
kubectl create deployment asset-testing-deployment --image alahari9/asset-testing:latest -o yaml --dry-run=client > helm/templates/deployment.yaml
#make sure docker is running in your local before executing below command
kubectl apply -f helm/templates/deployment.yaml
```

```shell
#to test the application create Nodeport and verify
kubectl create service nodeport asset-testing-np  --tcp=3030:8080 -o yaml --dry-run=client > helm/templates/nodeport.yaml
kubectl apply -f helm/templates/nodeport.yaml
#Get the nodeport and verify
kubectl get svc
```